Tuna Noodle Casserole

- 1 red bell pepper
- 4-5 scallions
- 1lb mushrooms (pre-sliced is easiest)
- 4.5oz parmigiano-reggiano cheese
- 3 cans of tuna (solid in water is best)
Preheat oven to 350F. Drain tuna.  Chop pepper to 1/2 inch dice. Slice scallions and mushrooms(if necessary). Grate cheese.

- 1lb box bowtie pasta (farfalle)
Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Cook pasta for 7 minutes.

- 1 stick butter
+ pepper
+ mushrooms
+ scallions
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan until sizzling, then cook pepper about 3 minutes until starting to soften.
Add mushrooms and scallions. Cook for 8-10 minutes until mushrooms have lost their moisture.

- 60g flour
- 1.5 cups chicken broth
- 3 cups milk
Stir in flour and cook about 3 minutes until raw smell is cooked off.
Add a splash of broth and stir until mixed evenly, then repeat with all of the broth.
Add milk and stir to mix. Bring to a boil, then simmer for about 3 minutes and remove from heat.

- 1/4 tsp cayenne
+ tuna
+ 3/4 cheese
Add cayenne, tuna, and about 3/4 of the cheese. Mix well. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

- 1/2 cup breadcrumbs
+ remaining cheese
+ sauce
+ pasta
Spray casserole dish.
Combine sauce and pasta and pour into casserole dish.
Top with breadcrumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake for 25-30 minutes until heated fully and breadcrumbs are browned.
Let rest for 5 minutes before serving.



